      div#faq.main_cont
        h1 FAQ
        div
          h4 How can I use the data?
          p A popup on each map links to the data's source and the local government's data policy.
          p If you have questions or need the data for anything mission-critical, ask the local government directly.
          hr

          h4 What if my city isn't included?
          p Reach out to your city and county GIS departments. It's possible that they may not have buildings data, or that one may have better data than the other.
          p If you get permission to publish the data freely on this site, please have an official send a written data policy.
          hr
          
          h4 Why would a city or county share their data on MajuroJS.org?
          p MajuroJS.org is a platform for officials, community leaders, student volunteers, and others to illustrate their neighborhoods, their work, and their plans on the web. For the people who trying to change their neighborhoods, it is a huge leap to get the detailed, comprehensive maps from the local government.
          p Publish your data on a site accessible and usable by citizens, without taxing your own website or technical support teams.
          hr
          
          h4 Does the site work with Internet Explorer?
          p All saved and finished maps should work with Internet Explorer 7 and above - this makes your maps available to most local government officials.
          p In the map editor, a color change control appears in place of the drag &amp; drop editor. Direct KML and GeoJSON downloads are unavailable until after you save your map.
          hr

          h4 How do I add my data?
          p Send a shapefile, KML, or a link to a page from your city's open data site.
          hr

          h4 Is this open source?
          p
            span The entire site is open source.&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/mapmeld/majurojs") Source code on Github
          p The background map (and the image at the top of this page) use data from OpenStreetMap.
          hr
          
          h4 Can I map a whole city with this?
          p Maps on Majuro.js are vector-based, so several hundred or thousands of buildings can slow down web browsers.
          p
            span For large projects, try downloading the data as KML, then upload it to&nbsp;
            a(href="http://cartodb.com") CartoDB
            span &nbsp;and edit it through&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/NeighborDiff") NeighborDiff
            span .
          hr

          h4 How did this project get started?
          p
            span I am Nick Doiron, @mapmeld on&nbsp;
            a(href="http://twitter.com/mapmeld") Twitter
            span &nbsp;and&nbsp;
            a(href="http://github.com/mapmeld") Github
            span . Majuro.js is based on projects that I made for the City of Macon, GA during my Code for America fellowship, particularly:&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/geodata-checkout") GeoData Checkout
            span &nbsp;and&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/NeighborDiff") NeighborDiff.
        
        div#finish_line_cont

